### Environment variables - different environments
# You can switch between environments by clicking on the environment dropdown
@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080
@contentType = application/json

### 1. Create a new merchant
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/merchants
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "merchant@example.com",
  "businessName": "Example Store",
  "defaultCurrency": "EUR",
  "emailNotifications": true
}

> {%
    // JavaScript response handler
    client.global.set("merchantPublicId", response.body.id);
    client.global.set("merchantId", "1"); // In real app, get from response
    client.log("Created merchant: " + response.body.id);
%}

### 2. Get merchant by public ID (using variable from previous response)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/merchants/{{merchantPublicId}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

### 3. Create verification request (resend verification email)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/merchants/{{merchantPublicId}}/verification-requests

### 4. Verify email (simulated - in real app, you'd use the token from email)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/merchants/verification?token={{merchantPublicId}}
Accept: {{contentType}}

### 5. Update merchant settings
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/api/merchants/{{merchantId}}/settings
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "defaultCurrency": "USD",
  "emailNotifications": false,
  "smsNotifications": true
}

### 6. Get merchant status
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/merchants/{{merchantPublicId}}/status
Accept: {{contentType}}

### 7. Search merchants
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/merchants/search
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "merchant",
  "status": "ACTIVE",
  "page": 0,
  "size": 10
}

### 8. Deactivate merchant
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/merchants/{{merchantId}}/deactivation